---

When the user asks to map, audit, inspect, understand, or explain this
codebase, first read `agent/AGENT_GUIDE.md` and follow that portable workflow.

Run Portolan before broad manual architecture claims. Start with
`portolan doctor`; use `portolan map --root . --out .portolan/run` once
available, or the guide's current-command fallback until then.

Answer from Portolan artifacts only. Preserve `unknown`, `cannot_verify`, and
`not_assessed` instead of guessing. Do not fetch network resources, mutate the
repository, or collect credentials unless the user explicitly approves that
boundary.
